import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['lat'] = pd.to_numeric(data['lat'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lat', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['lat'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitudes in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['lat'] = pd.to_numeric(data['lat'], errors='coerce')
    avg_lat = data['lat'].mean()
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lat', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(avg_lat, color='red', label=f'Average Latitude: {avg_lat:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average latitude in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['key'] = pd.to_numeric(data['key'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='key', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['key'].min(), color='red', label=f"Min: {data['key'].min():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['key'].max(), color='green', label=f"Max: {data['key'].max():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the range of keys in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
